title: For Sale:  Ruger .380 LCP
postcontent:
I am listing for sale a Ruger .380 LCP. Lightly used (less than 30 rounds total through it) but near daily carry. It has a pocket clip attached on the right side of the frame that allows for grip forward carry in the right front pocket of your jeans or a rear grip carry if you prefer to carry for your left hand. It also includes the original box, paperwork, trigger lock, cloth storage case and a DeSantis-brand Nemesis pocket holster. Excellent weapon for concealed carry as it is nearly invisible unless you wear a Speedo at the pool or beach and then you have more issues than a handgun could solve...otherwise, it's a very easily concealed weapon that is handy when anything larger would print through clothing or be an inconvenience to wear.

The holster in conjunction with the pocket clip help to keep the barrel lint and obstruction free while carrying. There are two areas of very light rust (appears to be surface only with no pitting) on the right and left rear of the slide near the slide serrations (please see photos for further detail) but the weapon is otherwise in excellent condition and the bore/crown of the muzzle are both pristine. Light rub marks on areas of the slide from being carried but blueing is solid throughout. The weapon was purchased with a seven round magazine standard and I have on additional ten round ProMag-brand magazine I will include. I will also include a partial box of Glaser Pow'r Ball .380 70 grain self-defense ammunition with the sale. 

Open to offers for an outright cash sale and/or partial trades for other firearms with me offering cash in addition to this item if necessary. Please be able to provide proof of your legal eligibility to own/purchase this item (ie: valid ccw permit, over the age of 21, etc.) and I will have a bill of sale requiring a signature from the buyer at the time of purchase. Thanks for looking and look forward to hearing from anyone interested.

title: For Sale:  Remington model 512 Sportmaster made in June of 1946.
postcontent:
Made in June of 1946. Remington model 512 sportmaster. This is a less frequently seen tube fed bolt action that shoots all flavors of .22. Short, long or long rifle. It holds 22-rounds (22 short) 17-rounds (22 long) 15-rounds (22 LR) It's action is as smooth as warm silk & it is a dead on accurate rifle if you do your part. It has a fire/load indicator. When the bolt is charged, the red painted end of the firing pin protrudes from the back of the bolt showing that it is ready to fire. I regularly pull 2-3" groups at 100 yards, not a boast, just simple fact. 25-inch (64 cm) barrel, 43 in (110 cm) overall length. Weigh 6 lbs. White metal bead front, open rear sight. The bluing is in 85%+, the stock has a few marks here & there, but nothing too drastic at all. The mill work on the backside of the bolt is beautiful, you just don't see work like this on modern rifles. This is not your garden variety .22 plinker. It is in 100% original condition and in my humble opinion one heck of a nice slice of firearms history. Just think about everything happening when this old fella was made/bought. Mainly, our boys were coming home from Europe and settling back into their interrupted lives, among many other things.

I have many detailed pics, email me to see them. 

Thank you for your time.

title: For Sale:  1895 Winchester  30-1903 cal. RARE!
postcontent: The model 95 is a rare gun made famous by Teddy Roosevelt. The .30-1903 was adopted by the Army in 1903 to replace the aging .30 Army (.30-40 Krag) which had been adopted in 1892. Winchester first offered the model 1895 in the .30-03 cartridge in 1905. Unfortunately, the '03 cartridge became all but obsolete only a year later with the adoption by the Army of the .30-06 in 1906. (Commercial ammo for the '03 was made up until WWI.) It wasn't until 1908 that Winchester produced the 1895 in '06.  This pictured gun was born in 1912. Bright bore with great rifling, 50% bluing, wood has no cracks and has great wood to metal fit, originally had a Lyman 21 sight which was removed and a rear marble was installed. I would replace marble with a Lyman 21 to bring it back to originally configuration. This gun is also more desirable because it does not come with the standard 28" barrel, but the 24".

title: For Sale/Trade:  M44
postcontent:
This is by far one of my favorite firearms. This is for the big boys that can handle shoulder firing the 7.62x54R round. 

This 1944 M44 is in excellent condition. I no longer have the original stock however the composite stock it is fitted with fits and feels great when firing. 

The firearm has been very well taken care of with a great bore. It has amazing accuracy and is a fine piece of history. This design was originally made to deal with the urban warfare environment of late WW2. It is essentially a shortened version of the Mosin Nagant series of scout sniper rifles.  It has surprisingly low recoil given the power of the round it fires.  The muzzle bloom when firing heavy ball ammunition is also rather impressive! 

The firearm has it's original bayonet still attached and the spring is still very tight. 

I will include 200 rounds of ammunition along with the stock sleeve and sling shown in the picture. I also have two stripperclips and the original sight tool to include. 

As part of the deal if you would like to fire the weapon before purchase I can accommodate the request.  Fire one of these and you will never want to fire another rifle again. The accuracy is simply amazing and the power behind the massive 7.62x54R round is pure adrenaline. 


I will accept any reasonable offer or trade. Email or text REDACTED
